[
    {
        "content": "<p>A (additive) monoid ideal <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">I</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">I</span></span></span></span> is a set of an additive monoid <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span> such that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>I</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>M</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>I</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\forall x\\in I.\\forall y\\in M.x+y\\in I</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7335em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">I</span><span class=\"mord\">.∀</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mord\">.</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7335em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">I</span></span></span></span>. Does Mathlib have a definition for that?</p>",
        "id": 546352508,
        "sender_full_name": "Dexin Zhang",
        "timestamp": 1761097678
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think that would be <code>SubAddAction Mᵃᵒᵖ M</code></p>",
        "id": 546352688,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1761097834
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SubAddAction#doc\">docs#SubAddAction</a></p>",
        "id": 546353302,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1761098396
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the docstring say scalar multiplication though</p>",
        "id": 546353369,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1761098426
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I promise you it's actually the additive action</p>",
        "id": 546353394,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1761098443
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it's like how an ideal is a <code>Submodule R R</code></p>",
        "id": 546353524,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1761098516
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's interesting! I'd also like to discuss the finiteness of a monoid ideal (like <code>Submodule.FG</code>), but there seems no definition of <code>SubAddAction.FG</code>?</p>",
        "id": 546354752,
